3. The flag images (SVGs) — original licenses retained
------------------------------------------------------

The `data/*.svg` files are, for the most part, NOT original works of this
repository. They are sourced from Wikimedia Commons and similar repositories,
and each retains the license under which it was originally published — most
commonly Public Domain (many official flags are not copyrightable) or
CC BY-SA. The source for each flag is recorded in the `sources` array of its
companion `data/<id>.json` file; consult that source for the authoritative
license and attribution requirements of an individual image.

No blanket license is asserted over the SVGs, because this project is not in a
position to grant one.

Trademark note: some emblems that appear on these flags (for example the Red
Cross / Red Crescent, the Olympic rings, and the NATO compass rose) are
protected by trademark and other laws independent of copyright. A free
copyright license on the SVG does not grant any right to use such emblems as
marks. These restrictions are outside the scope of this repository's licenses.
